cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.DM 

The paper presents a mathematical model and algorithmic solutions for the control problem in Condorcet voting. This involves the use of relation algebra and tool-supported programming language. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves algorithmic solutions. The paper also involves mathematical modeling and logic, which suggests it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of game theory and decision-making also suggests it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
